    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Rev. Mr I. Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Chicago</placeName>
                <date>March 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your esteemed favor of <date>18'</date> of last month is<lb/> before
                me, in reply to which I would like to treat of business first<lb/> &amp; of
                    <sic>miscellanious</sic> things afterwards. We are owing you incl. The<lb/> now
                ending vol. of the Occident $11.00, of which we have to deduct an<lb/> outlay for
                postage on the <date>23' March 1848</date> for books send to <persName>S.
                    Coh.</persName> Here<lb/> $—73 remaining $10.72, for which please to find an
                order to <placeName>N. Y.</placeName><lb/> enclosed, acknowledging its receipt in
                the next Occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your bill against <persName>S. Coh</persName> we have
                presented,<lb/> to which he replied as follows: I have remitted <persName>Mr
                    Leeser</persName> on the<lb/>
                <date><hi rend="underline">23' Jan 1848</hi></date> by you (respect.
                    <persName>Kohn</persName>, the same having been send in the letter<lb/> ordering
                the Occident) Three Dollars, then again I have receipt for<lb/> Three Dollars in the
                Occident of <date><hi rend="underline">June 1849</hi></date>, &amp; Six Dollars were
                send<lb/> by me to <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> some time in <date>Febr.</date>
                Last, which makes up the 12<lb/> Dollars, the amount of the bill. I hope it is in
                order, please<lb/> to write about it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In regard to your retiring from your office<lb/> last fall, I felt
                sorry when reading of it, there must have been<lb/> a serious misunderstanding
                between you &amp; your congr. to have caused<lb/> such a step, as far as I could
                learn, you acted the part of a<lb/> man of self respect by retiring. I regret very
                much, that I<lb/> could not do much with your circulars, to procure you new
                subscribers<lb/> there is too much <sic>indifferism</sic> amongst <add>יהודים</add>
                about their holy Religion<lb/> its defenders, or any thing out of trade, it is
                    <sic>realy</sic> deplorable, but<lb/> let us hope for better in the future. I
                have always looked<lb/> upon the Occid. as a welcome visitor, I like its tendency
                &amp; spirit<lb/> &amp; shall always peruse any of the volumes with pleasure &amp;
                satisfaction.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">But <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> I would <sic>advice</sic> you one
                thing<lb/> that if you do wish more subscribers for your Occ. or weekly<lb/> paper
                about to be published, do come out on a Editors Tour<lb/> to the west, &amp; by
                personally soliciting subscribers to your Periodicals</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">you will get 10 subscribers, to one you might get without<lb/> it.
                If you start after <add>פסח</add> &amp; go to <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <placeName>Utica</placeName><lb/>
                <placeName>Syracuse</placeName>
                <placeName>Rochester</placeName>
                <placeName><sic>Bufalo</sic></placeName>
                <placeName>Erie</placeName>
                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>
                <placeName>Sandusky</placeName>
                <placeName>Toledo</placeName>
                <placeName>Detroit</placeName><lb/>
                <placeName>Milwaukee</placeName>
                <placeName>Chicago</placeName>
                <placeName>Peru</placeName>
                <placeName>Pevria<add>?</add></placeName>
                <placeName>St Louis</placeName>, &amp; then down the
                <placeName>Miss.</placeName><lb/> &amp; <placeName>Ohio</placeName> up towards
                    <placeName>Cincinatti</placeName> &amp; home again, I will warrant you<lb/> a
                great many new names on your Lists, &amp; they pay all, which<lb/> is a principal
                thing. From <placeName>Albany West</placeName> you will find<lb/>
                <add>יהודים</add> in every town or City of little importance, who will take<lb/>
                your Occ. if they see you &amp; the paper. There area great many<lb/> who never
                heard of it, do come out &amp; show it to them, tell them<lb/> that it is a
                necessary Book in their families, particularly for<lb/> those who live isolated in
                places where there are only a few<lb/> &amp; no <add>קהלה</add> or Synagogue. Please
                look on the maps and<lb/> note every little town from here down the
                    <placeName>Illinois River</placeName> to <placeName>St Louis</placeName><lb/>
                &amp; from there on the <placeName>Miss.</placeName> &amp; then to
                    <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> &amp; you will find<lb/>
                <add>יהודים</add> in every town of importance, who will take your paper<lb/> if you
                present it yourself. The Exp. of <sic>travelling</sic> will come out<lb/> of it.
                This is a friendly advice of mine, you may take it<lb/> into consideration, it is
                given gratis, &amp; with the best intentions.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">They are at present forming a Congreg. at <placeName>Detroit<lb/>
                    Mich</placeName>, another has been started at <placeName>Milwaukee</placeName>,
                where there<lb/> are a great many families congregated from
                    <placeName>Bohemia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Here we began a <add>קהל</add> 3 years ago with 15 members<lb/> we
                now number 40 paying members, have a Burial Ground, &amp; by<lb/> building a
                Synagogue now, we are under an Expense of ca<lb/> 2200 Dollars to come out of the
                pockets of the members. There<lb/> are a good many things besides building a
                Synagogue to be wished<lb/> but patience &amp; perseverance will accomplish a great
                many things.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">By and bye, the Asmonean lately had an article<lb/> from a Corresp.
                from here, in which it states that by the liberality<lb/> of the
                    <placeName>NY.</placeName> merchant we are enabled to go on with our work<lb/>
                of building, this is not a fact, all we got from <placeName>NY.</placeName> Was<lb/>
                from <hi rend="underline">60 to 65 Dollars</hi>, honor to whom honor is due!</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Another thing! Could you not publish those several<lb/> =
                    <persName>Dias</persName> letters = in <sic>Phamplet</sic> form? <sic>they</sic>
                would sell <hi rend="underline">well</hi><lb/> every traveling <add>יהודי</add> in
                the <placeName>M. S.</placeName>
                <sic>wuld</sic> buy one I warrant you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you would try to give in your next volume of<lb/> the Occident
                some more light reading for children, some<lb/> extracts from <add>מדרש</add>,
                little anecdotes, little parables cc suitable<lb/> for the young, it would be some
                improvement, &amp; lead to more<lb/> subscribers. There are a great many who do not
                like always<lb/> grave matters or articles requiring thought &amp; study, some
                lighter<lb/> food will sometimes be more acceptable.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your Editions of <add>חמושים מחזרים תפילות</add> cc you will<lb/>
                also have <sic>oportunity</sic> to sell, if you should resolve to make a<lb/>
                Western Tour.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">About those <add>תפילות</add> you send by <persName>Mr
                    Goldsmith</persName>
                <placeName>NY</placeName><lb/> I never got them, neither are they with any of the
                booksellers<lb/> here. Finally <persName>Mr Leeser</persName>, I shall be in
                    <placeName>NY.</placeName> on or about<lb/>
                <add>פסח</add>, &amp; should be very happy to make your personal acquaintance<lb/>
                should you come there, you will easily find me by inquiring<lb/> after me. Please to
                excuse my long epistle, any faults<lb/> in the writing of it, I am only a German
                    <sic>decendant</sic> of <add>אהרן הכהן</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">A Kohn</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
